invalid type: string "1. Verify the MySQL root password you‚Äôre using is correct.  \n2. If the password has changed or you don‚Äôt want to use root, create a dedicated user:  \n   ```sql\n   CREATE USER 'app_user'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'StrongPassword!';\n   GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON your_database.* TO 'app_user'@'localhost';\n   FLUSH PRIVILEGES;\n   ```  \n3. Update\u{202f}`application.yml`ˇˇ